More newsletters | More sportsFor a while, it felt like the Warriors were something completely novel: a dominant sports team with a refreshing lack of ego or internal conflict.
Sure, Draymond Green and Steve Kerr would get into it from time to time, but most spectators were largely impressed with the way they seemed to play with such joy.
